    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Band 8  439 GHz</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to search for 439 GHz H2O line emission toward the nearby AGN, Circinus galaxy. The galaxy shows the strongest flux density of 22 GHz H2O maser. Hagiwara et al. (2013) detected 321 GHz H2O maser in the galaxy in the ALMA Cycle 0 Program. The 439 GHZ H2O emission is radiatively pumped at the dust temperature of about 300K.
It is thus likely that the 439 GHz maser is excited around the nucleus
of the galaxy, possibly at &lt; 0.1 pc from central engine.</prj:note>
