    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Band 7 325GHz</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to search for H2O maser emission at 325 GHz transition 
in Circinus galaxy upon the first detection of H2O maser at 321 GHz transition in the ALMA Cycle 0 observations by Hagiwara et al. (2013).
Since the upper state energy of the 325 H2O line (Eu/k = 470 K) is 
lower than that of the 321 H2O line (Eu/k = 1862 K), the 325 H2O should be able to be detected. By detecting the 325 H2O line, we will investigate the distribution of the maser in the fulture cycles at 20 mas resolution to explore appropriate line tracers around cenral engine in AGN.

</prj:note>
